/**/This code represents a simple To-Do List App built with HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. Here's a concise breakdown suitable for a GitHub repository:

Features:
HTML Structure:
Contains a text input for adding tasks and a button to add them to the list.
Tasks are displayed as a list (<ul> element).
CSS Styling:
Styled using an external style.css file for layout and design.
JavaScript Functionality:
Interactivity (e.g., adding tasks) is managed via an external script.js file.
Repository Files:
index.html: The main structure of the app.
style.css: Defines the design and appearance of the app.
script.js: Implements the app's interactivity.
images/icon.png: Optional icon displayed in the header.
Setup Instructions:
Clone the repository.
Place all files (HTML, CSS, JS, and images) in the same folder.
Open index.html in a browser to use the app.

CODE-------->>>>>>>>>

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>

<head>
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
    <title>To-Do List App Easy Tutorials</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>

<body>
<div class="container">
    <div class="todo-app">
        <h2>TO-DO LIST <img src="images/icon.png"></h2>
        <div class="row">
            <input type="text" id="input-box" placeholder="Add your text">
            <button onclick="addTask()">Add</button>
        </div>
        <ul id="list-container">
            <!--<li class="checked">Task 1</li>
            <li>Task 2</li>
            <li>Task 3</li>-->
        </ul>
    </div>
</div>
<script src="script.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
